Three members of parliament from north rift region are now accusing deputy president William Ruto and his allies of being behind the woes facing maize farmers. The MPs, Joshua kutuny, Alfred keter and Silas tiren called for thorough investigations into the leaders and that anyone found culpable in the current maize crisis prosecuted. The mps are also demanding a review of maize prices from the proposed ksh 2,300 to ksh 3,600